RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 1 1 1/16M Turf CR: 76. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 28000. FOR FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $32,000 OR LESS OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $32,000. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since March 23 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since February 23 Allowed 4 l bs. Claiming Price $32,000 (Races Where Entered For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Condition Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROYAL DAME raced in the two path around the first turn, pressed the pace on the outside up the backstretch, shook clear while saving ground around the far turn and drew off in the stretch. SUSIE'S SAVER raced in the three path around the first bend, chased the leaders on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the far turn and kept on to the wire, no match for the winner. HAPPY UNION raced off the pace on the inside through the opening half mile, continued to save ground around the far turn and improved position in the lane, no match for the winner. LOVE FOREVERAFTER raced in the two path early, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the four path, began a bid nearing the quarter pole and was outkicked in the stretch. ALWAYS ROYAL saved ground around the first bend, raced in the middle of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, came around the second turn in the three path and faded from there. NINETY NINE saved ground around the first turn, led the way on the inside up the backstretch, dropped back while saving ground around the far bend and continued to tire in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 70. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 23 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Races Where Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Registered Florida Breds Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BARBARA led the way up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the turn and kicked clear in the lane, holding that margin to the wire. PEEP'S DAY tracked the leader on the outside through the early going, came around the bend in the two and three path, began a bid approaching the quarter pole and chased the winner home, the best of the rest. LUSCIOUS chased the pace setter on the inside up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the two path and was outkicked in the lane. QUALITY TOO SPARE raced off the pace up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and never threatened.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 3 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 57. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, For Each $1,000 To $8,000 1 lb.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRAND ARROW bumped lightly with the horse to his inside at the start, raced in the three path around the first turn, trailed the field up the backstretch, continued around the far bend still in the three path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground quickly to sweep clear late. LA DAME DE FER raced off the pace on the outside through the opening half mile, began a bid from the four path coming around the second turn, dueled while lugging in mildly in upper stretch and chased the winner home from there. POWERFUL NATIVE brushed mildly with the horse to his outside leaving the gate, raced in the two path early, settled in the middle of the pack between horses for the run up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the three path and kept on to the wire. ANGELIC STORM saved ground around the first turn, raced in the middle of the pack on the inside up the backstretch and around the second bend and finished evenly. WINE WITH A ROSE raced in the two path around the first turn, chased the leader up the backstretch, continued around the far turn still in the two path and weakened in the stretch. POLITICAL ASTRAY angled over to save ground around the first turn, led the way up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the far bend and tired in the lane.

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Eric Martin Waller & Sharon Joy Waller

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 4 5F Turf CR: 92. Claiming Purse 20500. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 23 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since February 23 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered) (Condition Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THATSAFACTJACK led the field throughout, raced in the two path around the turn and held that margin to the wire. FACTION CAT chased the leader on the inside early, saved ground around the bend and kept on to the finish. BAM BAM BLU stalked the pace setter on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, came around the turn in the three path and chased on to the wire. COMMODORE BARRY raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the three path and improved position in the lane. JOYFUL HEART raced in the middle of the pack up the backstretch, navigated the bend from the three path and faded in the lane. SHANGHAI WARRIOR raced off the pace on the outside through the opening stages, continued around the bend in the four path and made no bid.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 67. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DUDESFIRSTDARLING led the way on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the turn, kicked clear in midstretch and held that margin to the wire. MY BATON ROUGE veered in and bumped with the horse to her inside at the start, settled in the middle of the pack for the run up the backstretch, launched a bid from the four path coming around the turn and chased the winner home in the lane. UCAPTURED AERO bumped with the horses to both sides leaving the gate, tracked the leader up the backstretch, came around the turn in the three path and kept on in the stretch. LIVELY REMARK raced in the middle of the pack between horses up the backstretch, continued around the bend in the three path and finished evenly. FLASH DEAR bumped with the horse to her inside at the break, raced off the pace early, came around the turn in the two path and showed no kick. ROMAN PRINCESS bumped with horses to both sides and was blocked leaving the gate, trailed the field up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the turn and made no bid. PLANE JANE pressed the pace on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, saved ground around the bend and tired in the stretch.

ENTRY.OWNER: Tropic Lightning Racing LLC and Seltzer Edward A

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 6 1M Turf CR: 76. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $16,000. The Same Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Started For Less Than $16,000 And Since Then Hav e Finished 2nd Or 3rd For $16,000 Or More.). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and Forty Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AWESOME HONOR raced in the three path around the first turn, pressed the pace on the outside up the backstretch, dueled while saving ground around the far turn, kicked clear in the lane and held off a closer at the wire. PRALINE'S CAT raced in the three path early, stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the far turn still in the three path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground late to narrowly miss. O ROMEO led the field while saving ground around the first turn and up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the far bend and gave way in the final furlong. DAD'S ON A ROLL saved ground early, raced in the middle of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn and finished evenly. SOMNUS chased the leader on the inside through the opening half mile, continued around the far turn still in the two path and faded from there. TURESKIS raced off the pace on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the three path and made no bid. CHAMPAGNE SHORES saved ground early, trailed the field up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far bend and was not a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 7 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 75. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since March 23 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Races Where Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BAM BAM WARRIOR raced in the four path around the first turn, stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the four path coming around the turn, gained ground steadily in the stretch and pulled clear late. SANDY DUDE raced in the two path early, trailed the field up the backstretch, continued around the far bend in the three path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground late. KINGSTOWN raced in the two path around the first turn, dueled on the inside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the three path around the far turn and in the lane and was caught late. TAPINTOYOURBEER saved ground while racing off the pace through the opening half mile, continued around the far turn in the four path, launched a bid passing the quarter pole and improved position from there. BLACK LIMO raced in the three path early, chased the frontrunner on the inside up the backstretch, continued around the second bend in the two path and weakened in the lane. CEDAR BEACH saved ground around the first turn, pressed the pace on the inside racing up the backstretch, dropped back from the rail coming around the far turn and continued to fade from there. DIAMOND LUCKIE dueled from the three path around the first turn and up the backstretch, dropped back while saving ground around the second turn and tired further in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 8 1M Turf CR: 85. Allowance Purse 28000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since February 23 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race S ince January 23 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $25,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances) (Condition Eligibility). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Milea nd Forty Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SATURDAY NITE GIRL raced at the back of the pack in the four path through the opening half mile, angled in to began a bid from the rail coming around the far turn, kicked clear in the stretch and held that margin to the wire. SWEET DUTCHESS saved ground early, raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, began a bid from the four path coming around the far turn and gained ground late. ASTERS D'ORO raced in the two path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack for the run up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the far bend and improved position in the lane. THUNDER BUGGY saved ground around the first turn, led the way on the inside up the backstretch and around the second turn and weakened in the final furlong. GLITTER BAY raced in the three path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch off the pace on the outside, navigated the far bend from the four path and improved position mildly in the lane while never truly threatening. LALOBA FEROZ was pinched back leaving the gate, raced at the back of the pack in the three path through the opening half mile, moved up from the five path coming around the far bend and passed tiring horses in the lane. HIGH VIBES raced in the two path around the first bend, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack, came around the far turn in the four path and faded from there. MY MAGGIE MOO trailed the field while saving ground around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the two path and showed no kick. FAMILY BAND raced in the three path around the first turn, chased the leader between horses up the backstretch, continued around the second turn in the two path and tired in the stretch. SINGALONG KAYLA raced in the four path around the first turn, stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, began to drop back while racing in the two path around the far turn and continued to tire from there.
